workflow.name: Daily Import Yesterday's Forex Factory Calendar to Google Sheets with Telegram Alerts
workflow.description:
## **Overview**

This n8n workflow automatically **fetches the Forex Factory calendar for yesterday** using **Rapid API**, then saves the data to a connected **Google Sheet** and sends **Telegram alerts** for high and medium impact events.

It runs **daily on schedule**, collecting key fields such as **currency, time, impact, and market indicators**, and organizes them for easy tracking and analysis. Perfect for **forex traders** and **analysts** who need quick access to reliable market data from the **previous day‚Äôs events**.


## ‚úÖ **Tasks**


* ‚è∞ Runs automatically every day
* üåê Fetches **yesterday‚Äôs Forex Factory calendar** via Rapid API
* üßæ Collects key data fields: **year, date, time, currency, impact, actual, forecast, previous**
* üìä Saves all records to **Google Sheets** for tracking and analysis
* üö® Sends **Telegram alerts** for high and medium impact events
* ‚öôÔ∏è Keeps your market data updated and organized with **no manual work required**

## **üõ† How to Use**

* üìÑ **Create a Google Spreadsheet**  
  Create a new spreadsheet in Google Sheets and add two sheets: **High Impact** and **Low Impact**.  
  Connect it to your **Google Sheets** nodes in n8n.

* üåê **Find the API on Rapid API**  
  Go to [Rapid API](https://rapidapi.com/) and search for **Forex Factory Scraper**.  
  Subscribe to the API to get your access key.

* üîë **Connect Rapid API to n8n**  
  In your **HTTP Request** node, add the header below to authenticate your request:  


* üí¨ **Add Your Telegram Chat ID**  
In the **Telegram** node, paste your **Chat ID** to receive daily alerts for high-impact news.

* üïí **Activate the Workflow**  
Enable the **Schedule Trigger** to run daily.  
The workflow will automatically fetch **yesterday‚Äôs Forex Factory calendar**,  
save it to **Google Sheets**, and send **Telegram notifications**.

parameters.content:
## Forex Factory API

**Rapid API** gives us an API.  
The API provides the **exact day Forex Factory calendar** by its fields:

**Fields:**
- News Title  
- year  
- date  
- time  
- currency  
- impact  
- actual  
- forecast  
- previous

## Google Sheets Append Nodes

These nodes **append the Forex Factory calendar data** into the connected Google Sheet.

- **High Impact Sheet:** Stores events with *High* or *Medium* impact.
- **Low Impact Sheet:** Stores all *Low impact* events.

## telegram

**Add your Chat ID to it.**

It Sends High Impact News in one message.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
